ight except in Allah, but that it will expiate his sins\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27588,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/ramadan-expiation\/","url_meta":{"origin":34061,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Fasting this month expiates sins before it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever fasts the month of Ramadan, acknowledging its limits and guarding it as it should be, then it will expiate the sins which came before it.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 11524 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37802,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/05\/20\/expiation-sickness\/","url_meta":{"origin":34061,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Expiation of sins due to sickness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo believing man or woman, nor Muslim man or woman, is afflicted with illness but that Allah will curtail some of their sins by it.\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 508 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\